Defendant Travis Lavell Hazlett in court with attorney Richard J. Johnson.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing resumed.  Statements made by the state, defense, and defendant.

AS TO COUNTS 7 and 8: The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction on each count with Huber release for employment and treatment, Consecutive to each other and with any other time being served, with credit for 14 days on Count 7.  Good time allowed.  No Electronic monitoring allowed.  This sentence is STAYED until 12-17-14, 5pm.  Defendant instructed to report to the House of Correction.  Defendant to pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of probation period ordered in Counts 9 and 10.  Any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.     

AS TO COUNTS 9 and 10:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction on each count Straight time, Consecutive to each other and with any other time being served.  No Good time or Electronic monitoring allowed.   

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Participate with random urine screens;
*No illegal drugs or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No ownership/possession of any dogs for 5 years;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of probation period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.  

The Court orders the release of the dogs.  Defense disputes requested restitution amount; hearing date selected with the parties.  Defendant advised that he is to continue with Justice Point supervision until report in date of 12-17-14.  Appeal rights given. 
